Please remember that ALL athletes MUST BRING WATER to practice EVERYDAY or they cannot practice.

Any students that are fully remote or have remote learning days, must show their pre screening link to Amy or their coach upon arrival to the practice

ALL ATHLETES MUST WEAR MASKS TO AND FROM PRACTICE SESSIONS WHILE ON SCHOOL PROPERTY!!

Field Hockey-- 3;30-5:00
Football-- 3:30-5:00 (Varsity football field)
XC-- 3:00-4:30
Golf-- 3:00-4;30 at PVCC
Boys Soccer-- 3:30-5:00
Girls Soccer-- 3:15-4:45

Have a great weekend and I look forward to starting the 2020 Fall Sports Season Monday!!

shared_text:
Town of Orono
July 13 at 12:34 PM ·

It's almost Election Day! Public health information on in-person voting for tomorrow's State Primary:
• Voting machines and other electronics are sanitized throughout the day with specific products and processes to manufacturer specifications
• All surfaces are wiped down with disinfectant wipes
• Pens and/or styluses are cleaned or sanitized when necessary
• Pollworkers are provided safety gloves, masks and personal hand sanitizer
• Sanitizer is provided for voters
Voters, please do your part:
• Wear a mask
• Distance yourself from other voters and pollworkers
• Stay at home if you have a fever, respiratory symptoms, or believe you are sick. Even on Election Day, you can request an absentee ballot if you are not feeling well
• Practice hand hygiene: wash hands often with soap and water or use provided sanitizer (please make sure that it is "rubbed" in before touching equipment)
Thank you!

post_text:
Good morning Red Riot Family,

As part of the construction of the track/football complex, we had to remove the existing press box. However, we have found a use for the actual press box and will utilize it as the new Boosters Concessions down at the soccer-Field Hockey-Baseball-Softball area.

In order to make the building functional for what the Boosters provide, it will need some construction inside the building. This would include:

Closing in the walls where the studs are exposed
Adding both closed and open shelving for storage and counter space for appliances and serving
Removing one of the inner petition walls to open up the main serving area

Two to three people with a handy skill set would be more than enough and may take 2-3 days to accomplish. I will have Climo Electric come in and provide adequate electricity to meet their needs. All materials will be provided and will be on location.

If you would like to volunteer a few hours of your time to make over this building into our new OHS Boosters concessions, please contact AD Mike Archer. (marcher@rsu26.org)
text:
Good morning Red Riot Family,

As part of the construction of the track/football complex, we had to remove the existing press box. However, we have found a use for the actual press box and will utilize it as the new Boosters Concessions down at the soccer-Field Hockey-Baseball-Softball area.

In order to make the building functional for what the Boosters provide, it will need some construction inside the building. This would include:

Closing in the walls where the studs are exposed
Adding both closed and open shelving for storage and counter space for appliances and serving
Removing one of the inner petition walls to open up the main serving area

Two to three people with a handy skill set would be more than enough and may take 2-3 days to accomplish. I will have Climo Electric come in and provide adequate electricity to meet their needs. All materials will be provided and will be on location.

If you would like to volunteer a few hours of your time to make over this building into our new OHS Boosters concessions, please contact AD Mike Archer. (marcher@rsu26.org)

post_text:
We hold all our students in our hearts today as they try to make sense of the news and disinformation; as they struggle to find their voice and the voices of their peers. Operation Breaking Stereotypes (http://ow.ly/CUti50zVD7c) has been in Orono Schools, Old Town Schools, and Indian Island School helping students develop their self-awareness, kindness, and leadership.

This year Operation Breaking Stereotypes students from Orono Middle School and Leonard Middle School believe that we need to see our common humanity, but we also need to stop and listen and be aware of who each person really is — not the labels and expectations that the world puts on us, but the raw, open, beautiful qualities each of us carries close to our hearts. Please watch this video and let these students inspire you to begin creating your new, open, and connected world.

Thank you to Nathan Manaker, OHS graduate and current student at Emerson College, for creating this “window into identity”!
http://ow.ly/hEhH50zVD7e

Our librarian friends at UMaine's Fogler Library present the Misinformation Challenge - sign up for this game to discern fact from fake news about Covid-19.

Each day for 5 days, you will receive an email with one or two tasks designed to test your knowledge of the novel coronavirus, while having fun and learning something new. You'll spend time evaluating memes, doctors, news headlines, treatments, and some of the science behind the virus.

The challenge will take place from May 25th to May 29th. To join, sign up
online
<https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSfAQonzYDHJp6I27Ju-Te4U5Zrt3jkIAI8G5opSI71yqnJXLg/viewform>. Any questions? Email Ms. Jackson Sanborn.

post_text:
Sometimes you just need to see a friendly face:
OHS staff did just that yesterday. Organized by Ms. Terrill, staff spent 5 hours parading through Orono, to Pushaw, to Bangor, to Glenburn (also, who knew Glenburn was so big), Milford, and Bradley. They honked the horns, did all the waving, & blew many many kisses. It was so great to see all the senior citizens come out and wave at the passing cars.

post_text:
And now a word from the OHS Student Council:

Red Riot Rallying Cry:

Orono High School has it's last official day before April vacation tomorrow and it is school pride day. We may not be having a typical school year, but we have an incredible staff and student body. We may not be able to have a real Riot Rally, but let's rally together. Let's all be sure to dress up in our Orono gear and post pics. Let's do it for our beloved seniors, for our amazing teachers, admin team and our community. Let's do it because we have pride in our school and ourselves. Show us your t-shirts, your hoodies, your riot socks! If you are a current Riot, or a die-hard Red Riot from way back, send us your pics! Post them on social media, send them to kemerson@rsu26.org and let's all use

#OronoStrong20
#GoRiots
#RiotPride
#edchatme

Let's show more pride than any other school could even imagine, Riots!

Students and staff from the Asa C Adams School and Orono Middle School are invited to participate in this School Spirit Day!

post_text: I'm pretty sure the phrase about April showers bringing May flowers didn't contemplate an April Nor'easter! Nonetheless, here we are! Due to widespread power outages caused by the storm, we will not hold remote learning today. Get outside (at your home) and enjoy the last snow of the season (fingers crossed on that one)! We will "see" you all back in our virtual classrooms next week!

post_text: Our food service team is prepping for today’s distribution of meals! Reminder that we are changing the days for distribution to two days per week beginning TODAY. Meals will be provided only on Mondays and Thursdays each week. We will package multiple meals for pick up on these days to bridge the span in between. Meals available at Asa Adams and the American Legion building from 9-12. Bus delivery available by request on these same days. We do plan to stay with this same schedule during April vacation week of April 20th! Let’s share some thanks and appreciation to our fantastic food service team for their hard work and dedication!

post_text: We've loaned our 3D Printers to the Challenger Learning Center where they're printing face shields for medical professionals along with other borrowed printers. We're so glad we can do this little thing to support our local healthcare workers!! A huge thanks to Melissa Barton for making the arrangements.
shared_text:
Challenger Learning Center of Maine
April 5 at 7:27 AM ·

That fun feeling setting up the army of 3D printers! This weekend we are getting setup, leveled, loaded with filament and ready for face shield production this week! Thank you to the following amazing schools for lending their 3D printers-RSU 26: Orono, UMaine RiSE Center, Maine Central Institute, Ellsworth Schools and RSU 25: Bucksport/ Prospect/ Orland/ Verona Island

post_text:
In an effort to proactively slow the spread of COVID-19 in alignment with other school districts in our area, we are announcing that RSU 26 schools will be closed beginning Monday, March 16 through Friday, March 27th. This closure is subject to change as the situation develops and new information becomes available. Staff will report to school on Monday to begin planning for continuity of instruction. More details will follow by Monday. In the interim, families and students should not come to school to gather materials; a plan will be communicated by Monday for how materials and remote learning instructions will be provided.

Please know we do not take this action lightly but feel it is in the best interest of the health of our students, staff, and community members.

The OMS annual Can Castle Competition is upon us! The OMS Student Council is asking fellow students to help make sure no child is without something to eat this holiday season. Non-perishable food donations are already being collected in every home room, but we need everyone's support. All donations will go to the Black Bear Exchange to help as many families as possible. The more we donate, the more people we can help! Please bring in any donations your family can offer before December 20. One person can't do it alone, but each of us can make a difference. “I alone cannot change the world, but I can cast a stone across the waters to create many ripples.”

Check out the pictures from last year's Can Castle Competition.
http://ow.ly/XZYM50xt03j

post_text: On November 13th, Dr. Elizabeth Allan, Associate Professor of Higher Education at the University of Maine, presented information about the Women's Suffrage Movement to students in Mrs. Bishop's 7th grade social studies class. She shared a powerpoint presentation and read a book to the students. The students then worked through a mock debate as though they lived during the early 1900's, before the passage of the 19th Amendment. This focus of this debate was whether or not women should have the right to vote. Mrs. Bishop would like to thank Dr. Allan for taking the time to visit and for sharing her knowledge with our students.

post_text: Asa C Adams School's Ms. Oldenburgh has been reading aloud the book "America's White Table" by Margot Raven (http://ow.ly/KByY30pRJtH) for over 10 years during her Veterans Day teaching. After the read aloud and discussion, she sets up the white table in the classroom for students. The year she had Sophia Neville, Sophia was very touched by the white table and went home and created her own. It always wonderful when a student is so inspired. Ms. Oldenburgh has invited Sophie, now a 6th grader at Orono Middle School, back each year to set the table and explain the symbolism of each piece on the table. The white table has been set up since the ending of the Vietnam War as a somber reminder of service men and women that never made it back to their loved ones.

Town of Orono
October 8, 2019 at 5:26 PM ·

STILLWATER AVE TRAVELERS TAKE NOTE!!

The City of Old Town is planning sewer line replacement project on Spring Street that will impact Stillwater Avenue travel from 10/13/19 until 10/18/2019.

SOUTHBOUND traffic from College Avenue to Bennoch Road will be ALLOWED at all times.

NORTHBOUND traffic heading from Bennoch Road to College Avenue on Stillwater Avenue will be PROHIBITED from 7 AM until 5:30 PM during the construction effort. Traffic will be ALLOWED from 5:30 PM - 7 AM.

This is the latest information from the City of Old Town as of 5:00 PM on 10/08/2019 and replaces the previously published information regarding a complete closure of Stillwater Avenue.

This important project will have an impact on Orono travelers and businesses. Remember that Stillwater Ave will remain open in both directions between Bennoch Rd and I-95 throughout the project so please make an effort to support the businesses during a construction period that is beyond their control!

post_text:
Please help us support a member of the RSU #26 community.
Vicki Lynch, the founder of the Orono Schools PreK program is on medical leave.

The family needs help with the extra expenses of a prolonged illness.

We are raising money in a variety of ways and the Orono Education Association/Maine Education Association is matching the raised funds.

Here's one way you can help. Buy a raffle ticket for this Red Riots cornhole game. It was handcrafted & donated by Nate & Meranda Case. Tickets can be purchased at Asa from Lisa Fox, Janet Metcalf, Kate Crane, Sandy Seavey, Nick Butler, Nate and Meranda Case, or from Deb White at OMS or from Shana Goodall at OHS. Tickets are 1 for $5 and 5 for $20. Raffle to be drawn on November 25, 2019.

post_text: The Orono High School field hockey team is running a fundraiser to raise money to pay for things like winter league and summer league. We are selling pints of Spencer's Ice Cream for $5 each, or you can get the special custom flavor "Red Riot Razzle Dazzle" (vanilla ice cream with a raspberry swirl) which is $10 for a quart. We are selling until Friday, August 23. Pints will be available for pickup on Friday, August 30th from 5-7pm in the parking lot behind the high school during our alumni field hockey game. You can place your order with Coach Dreher, Coach Espling, or any of our team members.

post_text:
The PowerSchool Registration form has been sent to the contact email/s RSU 26 has on file. Please check to see the email is from PowerSchool Registration. Please read the entire letter and details as the letter has in-depth instructions to completing the registration.

A few troubleshooting points to keep in mind. There is a lot of data of being processed so if you do not receive an email, first check your Spam folder to see if the email went there. If after 24 hours, you do not receive an email, please reach out to powerschooladmin@rsu26.org

Once you complete the form, do note there may be some time between submission and PS access. The staff at RSU 26 is working diligently to process the forms and data. Remember, you need to complete the form to get access to PS.

Thank you for your patience and assistance as we work through the final steps of transitioning to PowerSchool.

Town of Orono
May 22, 2019 at 9:18 AM ·

Three RSU 26 questions are on the ballot for the election being held on Tuesday, June 11th from 7:00am - 8:00pm at the Town Office upstairs in the Council Chambers. Orono residents may register to vote on the day of the Election. Absentee ballots are available at the Town Office in advance of the Election date.
Bond question sample ballot:

post_text: Congratulations to the OHS Show Choir who was recognized today at the Maine State Senate for their 2019 State Championship! The Show Choir performed the National Anthem to open the senate session and were fortunate enough to have some spare time to regale visitors with songs from this year's set. What a great way to cap off an incredible year for this fabulous group! Thanks to Senator James Dill for the recognition and Representative Ryan Tipping for the visit.
shared_text:
Cami Carter‎Orono High School Performing Arts
May 21, 2019 at 1:10 PM ·

We had such a great day at the Maine State Senate as they honored the OHS Show Choir for their 2019 State Championship! The Show Choir performed the National Anthem to open the senate session and were fortunate enough to have some spare time to regale visitors with songs from their set this year. What an incredible group of students and an incredible year! Thanks to Senator James Dill for the recognition and Representative Ryan Tipping for the visit.
